    - m_Type: 1
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Instructions
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "<b>1.</b>  In the <b>Scene</b> view, use Flythrough mode
          (WASD + right-click) to get the perfect view of the bouncing ball and your
          block towers. \n\n<b>2.</b>  Select the <b>Camera</b> GameObject in the
          <b>Hierarchy</b> window.\n\n<b>3.</b>  Press <b>Ctrl+Shift+F</b> (macOS:
          <b>Cmd+Shift+F</b>) to align the <b>Camera</b> GameObject with your current
          view. \n\n<b>Note:</b> With the <b>Camera</b> still selected, you could
          also go to the main menu and select <b>GameObject</b> > <b>Align with View.</b>\n\n<b>4.</b> 
          Enter Play mode to test the new camera angle. \n\nIf necessary, tweak the
          <b>Position</b>, <b>Rotation</b>, or <b>Field of View</b> property in the
          <b>Camera</b> component to get the perfect angle. \n\n<b>5.</b>  When you\u2019re
          happy with your camera angle, disable the <b>Cameras</b> window overlay.\n\n<b>Tip:</b>
          Trying to do these minor movements in the <b>Scene</b> view with Flythrough
          mode can be frustrating. Try lightly tapping on the WASD keys while holding
          the right mouse button to do small movements. You can also use the Q and
          E keys in Flythrough mode to go up and down."
      m_CodeSample: 
